<topic id="learned-words">
  <title>Learned Words</title>
  <body>
    <p>Spell checker engines rely on dictionary to decide that a word is correctly spelled. To tell
      the spell checker engine that an unknown word is actually correctly spelled, you need to add
      that word to its dictionary. There are two ways to do this:<ul>
        <li>Press the <uicontrol>Learn</uicontrol> button from the <uicontrol>Spelling</uicontrol>
          dialog box.</li>
        <li>Invoke the contextual menu on an unknown word, then press <uicontrol>Learn
            word</uicontrol>.</li>
      </ul>Learned words are stored into a persistent dictionary file. Its name is composed of the
      currently checked language code and the <filepath>.tdi</filepath> extension, for example
        <filepath>en_US.tdi</filepath>. It is located in the:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><filepath product="editor editorEclipse">[HOME_DIR]/Application
          Data/com.oxygenxml/spell</filepath><filepath product="developer developerEclipse"
          >[HOME_DIR]/Application Data/com.oxygenxml.developer/spell</filepath><filepath
          product="author authorEclipse">[HOME_DIR]/Application
          Data/com.oxygenxml.author/spell</filepath> folder on Windows XP.</li>
      <li><filepath product="editor editorEclipse"
          >[HOME_DIR]/AppData/Roaming/com.oxygenxml/spell</filepath>
        <filepath product="developer developerEclipse"
          >[HOME_DIR]/AppData/Roaming/com.oxygenxml.developer/spell</filepath>
        <filepath product="author authorEclipse"
          >[HOME_DIR]/AppData/Roaming/com.oxygenxml.author/spell</filepath> folder on Windows
        Vista.</li>
      <li><filepath product="editor editorEclipse"
          >[HOME_DIR]/Library/Preferences/com.oxygenxml/spell</filepath>
        <filepath product="developer developerEclipse"
          >[HOME_DIR]/Library/Preferences/com.oxygenxml.developer/spell</filepath>
        <filepath product="author authorEclipse"
          >[HOME_DIR]/Library/Preferences/com.oxygenxml.author/spell</filepath> folder on Mac OS
        X.</li>
      <li><filepath product="editor editorEclipse">[user-home-folder]/com.oxygenxml/spell</filepath>
        <filepath product="developer developerEclipse"
          >[HOME_DIR]/com.oxygenxml.developer/spell</filepath>
        <filepath product="author authorEclipse"
          >[HOME_DIR]/com.oxygenxml.author/spell</filepath> folder on Linux.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      <note>To change this folder go to the <xref
          href="dictionaries-preferences-page.dita#dictionaries-preferences-page"><menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Spell Check</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Dictionaries</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> preferences page</xref>.</note>
      <note>To delete items from the list of learned words, press <uicontrol>Delete learned
          words</uicontrol> in the <xref
          href="dictionaries-preferences-page.dita#dictionaries-preferences-page"><menucascade>
            <uicontrol>Editor</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Spell Check</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Dictionaries</uicontrol>
          </menucascade> preferences page</xref>.</note>
    </p>
  </body>
</topic>
